So I showed you a little bit about how RStudio Connect works,

00:13:51.000 --> 00:13:52.000
how you can schedule things,

00:13:53.000 --> 00:13:54.000
some of the benefits of the admin pane

00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:57.000
and kind of seeing all the different automation that's possible.

00:13:58.000 --> 00:14:00.000
But what are the things you actually want to automate

00:14:01.000 --> 00:14:02.000
or things that you want to schedule?

00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:04.000
So there's a spectrum of needs here.

00:14:04.000 --> 00:14:05.000
In terms of things you might publish or automate.

00:14:06.000 --> 00:14:08.000
So you might have data updates like I just showed,

00:14:09.000 --> 00:14:10.000
like you have this ETL script

00:14:11.000 --> 00:14:14.000
where it's taking data from an API, saving it,

00:14:15.000 --> 00:14:16.000
and then appending it to a database

00:14:17.000 --> 00:14:19.000
or to some flat file where it's storing it for later.

00:14:20.000 --> 00:14:22.000
You might have a report that's running.

00:14:23.000 --> 00:14:25.000
So you just want to report on that data that's being updated.

00:14:26.000 --> 00:14:27.000
And actually, the part of automation here

00:14:28.000 --> 00:14:30.000
is creating a new report without you having to manually run it.

00:14:30.000 --> 00:14:32.000
And then delivering that to your colleagues.

00:14:34.000 --> 00:14:35.000
Another common use case we see

00:14:36.000 --> 00:14:38.000
is automated model training, updates, or batch scoring.

00:14:39.000 --> 00:14:41.000
So here you're either training an update, training a model,

00:14:42.000 --> 00:14:43.000
updating an existing model,

00:14:44.000 --> 00:14:47.000
or sending that model out to actually do some scoring.

00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:50.000
So like running through, forming some predictions

00:14:51.000 --> 00:14:53.000
and then saving those scores out into a database.

00:14:55.000 --> 00:14:57.000
And then lastly, something I'll talk about in a little bit

00:14:57.000 --> 00:15:00.000
is automated email delivery with warnings or updates

00:15:01.000 --> 00:15:02.000
or just nice to knows.

00:15:03.000 --> 00:15:05.000
So not only do you have the actual report running

00:15:06.000 --> 00:15:07.000
and connect handling the environments

00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:09.000
and the creation of those reports,

00:15:10.000 --> 00:15:12.000
but sometimes you want optional reports.

00:15:13.000 --> 00:15:16.000
Basically, you want to know only when something fails

00:15:17.000 --> 00:15:19.000
or only when something goes above or below a certain threshold.

00:15:20.000 --> 00:15:23.000
So by combining emails along with your reporting

00:15:24.000 --> 00:15:25.000
or your automation of data science,

00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:28.000
you can basically get your warning only when it's needed.

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:31.000
So you have a high signal to noise ratio

00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:33.000
and you're not just getting updates all the time,

00:15:34.000 --> 00:15:35.000
but only when something occurs.

